# Microservice Chassis: what the framework provides at runtime
direction: down

Service: "YOUR MICROSERVICE\n(business logic only)" {
  style: { fill: "#a5d6a7"; stroke: "#1b5e20"; stroke-width: 3; border-radius: 10 }
  Code: "@Controller\nclass OrderController {\n  placeOrder(req) { ... }\n  getOrder(id)    { ... }\n}\n\u2190 just business code\n  no boilerplate" {
    style: { fill: "#fff" }
  }
}

Chassis: "MICROSERVICE CHASSIS\n(framework: Spring Boot, Micronaut, Quarkus, Go-Kit, NestJS, etc.)" {
  style: { fill: "#bbdefb"; stroke: "#0d47a1"; stroke-width: 3; border-radius: 10 }

  Log: "Logging" {
    style: { fill: "#90caf9" }
    Detail: "structured JSON, correlation-ID,\n auto-injected fields"
  }
  Met: "Metrics" {
    style: { fill: "#90caf9" }
    Detail: "request count, latency,\n error rate, JVM stats,\n exposed at /metrics"
  }
  Tr: "Tracing" {
    style: { fill: "#90caf9" }
    Detail: "OpenTelemetry spans,\n inbound + outbound,\n propagates trace context"
  }
  Conf: "Config" {
    style: { fill: "#90caf9" }
    Detail: "env vars + remote config\n (Consul, Spring Cloud Config),\n hot-reload"
  }
  Disc: "Service\ndiscovery" {
    style: { fill: "#90caf9" }
    Detail: "register on startup,\n deregister on shutdown,\n client-side lookup"
  }
  CB: "Circuit\nbreaker" {
    style: { fill: "#90caf9" }
    Detail: "wraps outbound calls,\n trips on failure,\n half-open recovery"
  }
  Auth: "Auth" {
    style: { fill: "#90caf9" }
    Detail: "JWT verify, OAuth flow,\n role-based access,\n mTLS"
  }
  Health: "Health\nchecks" {
    style: { fill: "#90caf9" }
    Detail: "/health (liveness)\n /ready (deps available)\n /info (build version)"
  }
  Shut: "Graceful\nshutdown" {
    style: { fill: "#90caf9" }
    Detail: "SIGTERM \u2192 stop accepting,\n drain in-flight,\n deregister"
  }
}

Service -> Chassis: "uses (one library import)"

Note: "RESULT: A new service starts with ~50 lines of business code\nand inherits hundreds of lines of production-grade cross-cutting concerns.\n\nWHEN A NEW METRIC, LOG FIELD, OR TRACE PROPAGATION IS NEEDED:\n  \u2022 add to the chassis once\n  \u2022 every service that bumps the chassis version gets it\n  \u2022 NO change needed in business code\n\nDOWNSIDE: chassis ties services to a single platform/language.\nMulti-language orgs often switch to the SERVICE MESH model\n(language-agnostic cross-cutting via sidecar proxies) instead." {
  shape: rectangle
  style: { fill: "#e1bee7"; stroke: "#4a148c"; border-radius: 8 }
}
